00:28.174 --> 00:29.350
Everett Lynch.

00:29.602 --> 00:32.482
The media has christened
him "The Chameleon."

00:32.491 --> 00:35.625
He is a con man and a
murderer, who has targeted

00:35.627 --> 00:39.029
vulnerable middle-aged
women, single mothers.

00:39.031 --> 00:42.999
He's cut off their faces and
kept them as his trophies.

00:43.001 --> 00:46.036
A year ago, we nearly caught
him, but his daughter Grace...

00:46.038 --> 00:47.070
- Aah!
- Aah!

00:47.072 --> 00:48.572
She sacrificed herself

00:48.574 --> 00:50.340
so that he could get away.

00:50.342 --> 00:54.010
He broke Grace out of jail...

00:54.012 --> 00:55.178
And again...

00:55.180 --> 00:57.247
- Don't move.
- We almost caught him,

00:57.249 --> 00:58.882
if it hadn't been for his daughter.

00:58.884 --> 01:01.852
She'd do anything for him.

01:01.854 --> 01:04.453
But that wouldn't matter because Lynch

01:04.456 --> 01:08.024
couldn't bring himself
to take Grace with him.

01:08.026 --> 01:10.861
Maybe he couldn't bring
himself to keep using her

01:10.863 --> 01:13.997
the way his mother
Roberta had once used him.

01:13.999 --> 01:15.198
Oh, god!

01:15.200 --> 01:17.601
Everett Lynch remains at large.

01:17.603 --> 01:20.637
He is the FBI's most wanted,

01:20.639 --> 01:25.375
but there hasn't been any
sign of him for months.

01:29.081 --> 01:31.047
Hey. What's up?

01:31.049 --> 01:33.550
So I wanted you to be the first to know

01:33.552 --> 01:36.386
that my name is on a
short list of candidates

01:36.388 --> 01:38.588
being considered to fill
the director's chair.

01:38.590 --> 01:41.458
Emily, that's incredible.

01:41.460 --> 01:43.560
Oh, my... God.

01:43.562 --> 01:46.396
You're gonna be the
next director of the FBI.

01:46.398 --> 01:49.366
That still remains a definite maybe.

01:49.368 --> 01:52.702
Oh. ‭But I do know
that I want the job.

01:52.704 --> 01:56.740
But I would feel much better if
my first directive as Director

01:56.742 --> 01:59.643
was to appoint you
Unit Chief of the BAU.

01:59.645 --> 02:04.214
And I... I told you before,
that really does mean a lot.

02:04.216 --> 02:06.750
Enough to turn down being
special agent in charge

02:06.752 --> 02:08.952
of the New Orleans field office?

02:08.954 --> 02:12.255
Um... I'm not sure.

02:12.257 --> 02:13.778
Now I feel like I'm...

02:13.778 --> 02:15.802
I'm pressuring you into
staying, and that's not what I...

02:15.894 --> 02:19.763
Oh, no, no, no, see, and I'm feeling
like if I do go to New Orleans,

02:19.765 --> 02:21.932
you might not decide to make history

02:21.934 --> 02:23.900
as the first female head of the FBI.

02:23.902 --> 02:26.403
Oh, no, it's... Don't worry.

02:26.405 --> 02:29.339
If given the chance, I'm making history.

02:32.611 --> 02:35.912
The truth is, I don't think Lisa

02:35.914 --> 02:37.914
ever got over what happened to Phil.

02:37.916 --> 02:40.583
I mean, how could she, really?

02:40.585 --> 02:42.285
I'm so sorry, Luke.

02:42.287 --> 02:45.088
Lisa and I'll still be
friends, I mean, you know.

02:45.090 --> 02:48.091
We were always honest with each other.

02:48.093 --> 02:51.061
So, unfortunately, Rossi
can't make it tonight,

02:51.063 --> 02:54.597
but JJ just texted to say that she and
Emily are on their way over right now.

02:54.599 --> 02:56.566
Great, and thanks for hosting, Spence.

02:56.568 --> 02:59.102
Well, thank you for coming. I'm
embarrassed that it's taken me this long

02:59.104 --> 03:01.504
to have you guys over
to my house to hang out.

03:01.506 --> 03:04.507
Guys, I have something to say.

03:04.509 --> 03:07.510
An opportunity has
presented itself to me,

03:07.512 --> 03:11.081
and it is in the Silicon Valley.

03:14.519 --> 03:16.486
Global Stratagem Development.

03:16.488 --> 03:19.856
They're a private research group
that's expanding their stratagem

03:19.858 --> 03:23.360
to include combating
global environmental change.

03:23.362 --> 03:26.563
Wow, that sounds perfect for you.

03:26.565 --> 03:28.999
You get to do all the
good work you do at the BAU

03:29.001 --> 03:30.767
- without the gore.
- Yeah,

03:30.769 --> 03:33.636
ok, but... Are you
trying to get rid of me?

03:33.638 --> 03:35.305
No.

03:35.307 --> 03:37.173
I don't want anybody going anywhere.

03:37.175 --> 03:39.409
Right, and I don't want to go anywhere.

03:39.411 --> 03:42.145
I love... I mean, this
is my home. Not this room,

03:42.147 --> 03:44.848
but, you know, the BAU is

03:44.850 --> 03:47.350
and... Come on.

03:47.352 --> 03:49.419
We're family.

03:49.421 --> 03:51.421
Yeah,

03:51.423 --> 03:53.356
we're family,

03:53.358 --> 03:55.892
and our relationship to
each other is not bound

03:55.894 --> 03:57.861
by wherever we show up to go to work.

03:57.863 --> 04:00.497
If you have the opportunity
to do something you love,

04:00.499 --> 04:03.333
Penelope, you should
absolutely explore it.

04:08.507 --> 04:12.108
You know why you lasted longer
in this job than I ever did?

04:12.110 --> 04:16.478
You never really let the
unsub get inside your head.

04:17.749 --> 04:20.784
Is that your way of saying
you were better than me, Jason?

04:20.786 --> 04:23.520
You tell me. I'm inside your head.

04:23.522 --> 04:25.722
I'm the unsub.

04:25.724 --> 04:27.891
What do I want?

04:27.893 --> 04:30.593
You know, I never liked your games.

04:30.595 --> 04:32.562
I know. Remember?

04:32.564 --> 04:35.365
You and me? My yin to your yang?

04:35.367 --> 04:37.700
We were like Martin and Lewis.

04:37.702 --> 04:39.669
Forget the unsub. What do you want?

04:39.671 --> 04:41.704
I want you to ask yourself
that fundamental question

04:41.706 --> 04:43.940
that's been nagging
at you this whole time.

04:43.942 --> 04:45.442
I already answered it.

04:45.444 --> 04:47.410
I'm the unsub.

04:47.412 --> 04:50.280
Why didn't I kill you
when I had the chance?

04:56.588 --> 05:00.957
You kill me, you killed a federal
agent, and that brings down...

05:00.959 --> 05:03.460
That's the wrong answer.

05:03.462 --> 05:06.696
You'd never been in
that situation before.

05:06.698 --> 05:09.232
He had you on the ground,

05:09.234 --> 05:11.201
knife to your face.

05:11.203 --> 05:13.870
You resigned yourself
to the thought of dying.

05:13.872 --> 05:16.372
It scared the hell out of me.

05:16.374 --> 05:19.342
Everett Lynch didn't kill you

05:19.344 --> 05:22.312
because he looked in your
eyes and saw something

05:22.314 --> 05:24.280
of his father.

05:24.282 --> 05:27.784
Sons kill their fathers, Jason.

05:27.786 --> 05:29.919
Sure, they do, but not typically

05:29.921 --> 05:32.055
if they still have issues to work out.

05:32.057 --> 05:34.057
Lynch's dad is dead.

05:34.059 --> 05:37.060
His name was Douglas Moore.
He was an insurance man.

05:37.062 --> 05:39.229
Lynch's mother was trying to grift him

05:39.231 --> 05:41.397
and got careless and got pregnant.

05:41.399 --> 05:44.434
The guy drowned in a boating accident.

05:44.436 --> 05:46.870
Drowned, huh?

05:46.872 --> 05:49.873
Kind of like how Lynch would
describe Grace drowning.

05:49.875 --> 05:53.943
Oh, look, the Moore story checked out,

05:53.945 --> 05:57.113
unless...

05:59.451 --> 06:02.352
Roberta lied to me...

06:02.354 --> 06:06.523
And if she lied to me, she
probably lied to her son,

06:06.525 --> 06:10.226
and if he found out, he'd
want to find his father,

06:10.228 --> 06:12.695
don't you think?

06:25.510 --> 06:28.278
I need you to find my father.

06:28.280 --> 06:31.214
You start by tracking down these names.

06:33.985 --> 06:35.985
Consider it done,

06:35.987 --> 06:38.188
Mr. Myles.

06:49.467 --> 06:51.467
- Marilyn?
- Eddie,

06:51.469 --> 06:53.636
I need you. It's Jimmy. He, um,

06:53.638 --> 06:55.505
he... he hit me again, and I...

06:55.507 --> 06:57.340
Slow down. Where are you?

06:57.342 --> 07:00.009
Olivia and I are on our way to a motel,

07:00.011 --> 07:02.545
but I... I was just wondering

07:02.547 --> 07:07.684
if maybe the offer was still
good for us to move in together?

07:09.054 --> 07:11.020
- Uh, well...
- I know.

07:11.022 --> 07:14.157
I should... I should have never left
you hanging and gone back to him...

07:14.159 --> 07:17.293
It's not that. It's just I'm
out of town. I get back tomorrow.

07:17.295 --> 07:21.130
All right, so...

07:21.132 --> 07:23.833
So I'll come by and pick up you and
Olivia sometime tomorrow afternoon.

07:23.835 --> 07:26.402
Thanks, baby.

07:26.404 --> 07:28.404
I owe you.

07:28.406 --> 07:30.406
Bye.

07:38.283 --> 07:41.317
You have the most
remarkable facial structure.

07:41.319 --> 07:43.720
Has anyone ever told you that?

08:46.238 --> 08:49.439
Synced and corrected by <font color="#9d3141"><font color="#bb0000">deglinglau</font>
